==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: stick-tight
<hw>stick"-tight`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>any of several plants having seeds tipped with barbs
that may cling to fur or clothing, especially those of the genus
<gen>Bidens</gen>, also called <altname>bur marigold</altname>,
<altname>beggar-ticks</altname>, and <altname>Beggar's ticks</altname>,
which have prickly flattened achenes.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a seed from a sticktight{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sticky</ent>⟦br⟧
